 fantastic tax break wealthy taxpayers can now plan to transfer significantly greater amounts of wealth within their lifetimes without triggering gift tax this  million exemption is individual and portable meaning that couples could potentially gift up to  million to heirsthe annual gift tax exclusion is again  in  so one taxpayer may gift up to  each to an unlimited number of individuals this year with the lifetime exclusion of  million in mind those gifts can include tuition and payments for medical carecharitable ira donations are again permitted this isn’t an estate tax law per se but it factors into estate planning and it is certainly worth noting charitable ira rollovers are back in  we don’t know yet if they will be around in  there may be less financial incentive for families to make these rollovers given the much higher gift and estate tax exclusion this year but others will act on their altruismthe charitable ira rollover allows an ira owner age ½ or older to gift up to a total of  in ira assets to one or more qualified charities or nonprofit organizations a move that can count toward his or her annual rmd it has to be a direct transfer – the gift must pass directly from an ira sponsor to the charity the ira accountholder doesn’t get a tax deduction but he or she can potentially bypass the income tax on the distributioncharitable ira gifts made in january  can count for  the new law says that if you make a charitable ira transfer in january  you can elect to report the transfer on your  federal return additionally you are free to make another ira charitable rollover of up to  at some other point in  for the benefit of your  federal returnthe gst is back the generationskipping transfer tax was  in  but it returns at  in  the gst exemption is set at  million for  and it will be inflationindexed for in light of these interesting developments it might be time to review your estate planning strategyhave any questions feel free to give us a call at  or send us a